<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="will-n">will <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /wɪl/    美 /wɪl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 意志；决心：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>have <strong>a strong will</strong> 
有坚强的意志</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>an iron will / a will of iron</strong>
钢铁般的意志</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In spite of what happened, he never lost the will to fight.
尽管有如此遭遇，他从未丧失拼搏的意志。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 遗嘱：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>make a will</strong> 
立遗嘱</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>意愿：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was forced to sign the agreement <strong>against my will</strong>.
我被迫违心地在协议上签了字。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="at-will">at will</h3>
<p>1.<strong>随意地；随心所欲地：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They could travel at will, and the clock was not their master. 
他们能随意旅行，不受时间支配。</p><footer>2012 江西</footer></div></div>